<title>USA: RESEARCH ALERT - Televisa raised.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT - Televisa raised.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Deutsche Morgan Grenfell said Friday it had raised its rating for Mexican broadcaster Grupo Televisa to buy from hold.</p>
<p>-- In a report, the brokerage said potential for conflict among Televisa management had lessened substantially.</p>
<p>-- It also said it had adjusted its projections to account for various points, including postponement of asset sales, cost reductions and payment on $350 million in debt.</p>
<p>-- &quot;Management's decision to drastically reduce costs is very positive in our view, since high costs were a major concern.  This is the main reason for our upgrade.&quot;</p>
<p>-- The company's American Depositary Receipts were up 3/8 to 29-1/4.</p>
<p>((--Ian Simpson, Wall Street desk, (212) 859-1879))</p>
